How to Publish your Module on NPM

1. Create Index.ts file in root directory
   
2. Replace your tsconfig.json content with tsconfig.json.pub content.

3. Add rollup.config.js in root directory
   - Set dest file according to your umd.js name

4. Add following in Package.json file inside scripts
    "transpile": "ngc",
    "package": "rollup -c",
    "minify": "uglifyjs dist/bundles/datatable.umd.js --screw-ie8 --compress --mangle --comments --output dist/bundles/datatable.umd.min.js",
    "build": "npm run transpile && npm run package && npm run minify"

5. Execute npm run build (It will create neccesory packages in dist folder)

6. Add package.json inside dist folder (Content is in package.json.dist)

7. npm login => Sign Up and login locally

8. npm publish --access=public



** More Info: https://medium.com/@cyrilletuzi/how-to-build-and-publish-an-angular-module-7ad19c0b4464

